        "description": "Isotropic linear-elastic material model for Ti-6Al-4V validated against uniaxial coupon data; nonlinear contact (augmented Lagrangian) used at all interfaces. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison of predicted vs. measured load-displacement curves across all 11 specimens; systematic bias < 5% for all QoIs. Achieves Gradation 3: quantified model form uncertainty included in total uncertainty budget."
      },
      "rationale": "The isotropic linear-elastic constitutive model for Ti-6Al-4V was validated against uniaxial tensile coupon data from the same material lot. Nonlinear frictional contact (μ=0.3, augmented Lagrangian) was applied at all screw-rod and rod-block interfaces. Comparison of 11 predicted vs. measured load-displacement curves shows systematic bias of 3.2% in stiffness and 4.1% in yield force, both within the 5% acceptance criterion. Model form uncertainty is formally included in the simulation uncertainty budget."
    },
