        "description": "All material properties sourced from mill certificates for the production material lot. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of 5 representative screws (diameter, thread pitch, root radius). Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo sampling (n=1000) over measured property distributions. Achieves Gradation 3: uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "Material properties (E, ν, σ_y, σ_u) were obtained from mill certificates for the Ti-6Al-4V lot used in both bench testing and FEA. Geometric inputs were characterized by CMM measurement of 5 representative production screws, with measured tolerances used as input uncertainty bounds. Monte Carlo propagation (n=1000 samples) quantified the contribution of input uncertainty to each QoI, accounting for approximately 2.8% of total QoI variability."
