        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 protocol followed at both laboratories. Load frame calibration traceable to NIST within 12 months. Crosshead displacement rate 5 mm/min ± 0.5 mm/min. Single loading condition (compression-bending only); no torsion or lateral bending tested. Required Gradation 3 (multiple loading conditions); achieved Gradation 2 (single standardized condition with calibrated equipment)."
      },
      "rationale": "Both laboratories followed the ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol with NIST-traceable load frame calibration. However, only a single loading condition (compression-bending) was tested; torsional and lateral bending conditions were not included in this validation activity. This limits the achieved level to Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3. The shortfall is addressed in the decision record offset rationale."
