        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "FEA inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably matched to as-tested specimen characteristics. CMM measurements of tested specimens used to update nominal FEA geometry. Material properties from same lot as tested screws. Friction coefficient validated via separate coupon pull-out tests. Achieves Gradation 3: specimen-specific FEA inputs matched to measured test article properties."
      },
      "rationale": "CMM measurements of the 11 tested constructs were used to update the FEA geometry on a per-specimen basis (diameter, inter-screw span). Material properties were drawn from the same lot certificates. The friction coefficient at the screw-rod interface was validated via three independent coupon pull-out tests yielding μ = 0.29 ± 0.02, consistent with the FEA input of 0.30. This specimen-specific input matching satisfies Gradation 3."
    },
    {
