        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/relevance-qoi",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary ASTM F1717 performance endpoints directly linked to clinical failure modes (construct loosening, screw fracture). Documented traceability from clinical risk to QoI selection in the risk-benefit analysis. Achieves Gradation 3: QoIs explicitly linked to clinical risk endpoints with documented traceability."
      },
      "rationale": "The three selected QoIs map directly to the ASTM F1717 performance endpoints used in regulatory submissions. Construct stiffness is linked to micromotion-induced pseudarthrosis risk; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are linked to screw fracture and construct failure risk. Traceability from clinical failure modes to QoI selection is documented in the risk-benefit analysis (RBA-NCT-2024-03)."
